==English==
===Etymology===
From Latin ''[[erectio]]'', noun of action from perfect passive participle ''[[erectus]]'', from verb ''[[erigere]]'', from suffix ''[[e-]]'', '''out of''', + ''[[rigere]]'', + action suffix ''[[-io]]''
===Noun===
{{en-noun|erection|erections}}
# The [[build|building]] or putting up or together of something; [[construction]].
# Anything [[erect]]ed.
# In particular, a [[hard]] or [[stiff]] [[penis]].

